items.title: US takes nearly 10% Intel stake, clinching unorthodox deal
items.description: Under the agreement, the US will receive 433.3 million shares of common stock — representing 9.9% of the fully diluted common shares in Intel — according to a statement from the company.

items.title: Dow notches record high as Wall Street cheers Powell's speech
items.description: The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 846.24 points, or 1.89%, to 45,631.74, surpassing its most recent record close on December 4, 2024. The S&P 500 gained 96.74 points, or 1.52%, to 6,466.91 and the Nasdaq Composite gained 396.22 points, or 1.88%, to 21,496.54.

items.title: Market extends gain in second week; autos outperform
items.description: Indian rupee ended with marginal gains at 87.52 per dollar against the August 14 closing of 87.56.

items.title: Broader indices outperform; 66 smallcap stocks rally 10–33%
items.description: In this month of August so far, FII sold equities worth Rs 25,751.02 crore and DII bought equities worth Rs 66,183.51 crore.
